videos.headline: Topley to Dhruv Jurel, out Caught by Karthik!! A leg-side strangle. Full down leg, Dhruv Jurel flicks and edges it behind to Karthik. DK does not even celebrate as Siraj is all happy near him. Dhruv Jurel walks off shaking his head. Dhruv Jurel c Karthik b Topley 2(3)

Yash Dayal to Riyan Parag, out Caught by Kohli!! Soft dismissal. A short of length delivery on off, whipped straight to the fielder at mid-wicket and Kohli does not drop that. Riyan Parag falls for a cheap score. It's the timeout as well. Riyan Parag c Kohli b Yash Dayal 4(4) [4s-1]

Yash Dayal to Riyan Parag, out Caught by Kohli!! Soft dismissal. A short of length delivery on off, whipped straight to the fielder at mid-wicket and Kohli does not drop that. Riyan Parag falls for a cheap score. It's the timeout as well. Riyan Parag c Kohli b Yash Dayal 4(4) [4s-1]

Siraj to Samson, out Caught by Yash Dayal!! Siraj gets Samson and smiles with fists clenched at the batter. A short delivery at the body, Samson miscues the pull and Dayal at deep backward square leg takes it just an inch from the cushions. The leg was tantalisingly close but he ensured that he was fine. Some respite for RCB. Samson c Yash Dayal b Siraj 69(42) [4s-8 6s-2]

Topley to Jaiswal, out Caught by Maxwell!! That's a great start for RCB. Topley strikes with his second ball. Jaiswal's not having a great start to the season. He decides to walk down the pitch and Topley sees that, shortens the length and generates extra bounce, Jaiswal still goes for the pull and only manages a top-edge, Maxwell settles under it near mid-off and takes it safely. Jaiswal c Maxwell b Topley 0(2)

Chahal to Saurav Chauhan, out Caught by Jaiswal!! Second wicket for Chahal. Brave move from Samson to bowl him the 18th and Chahal has'nt disappointed. Saurav would feel slightly disappointed. This was short and outside off, he shuffles and slaps it straight to extra cover, Jaiswal needed a couple of attempts to hang on. Saurav Chauhan c Jaiswal b Chahal 9(6) [6s-1]

Nandre Burger to Maxwell, out Bowled!! Cleaned up! Maxwell's woes with the bat continues.. The stage was set for him to explode but it is him who explodes. Maxwell b Nandre Burger 1(3)

Chahal to du Plessis, out Caught by Buttler!! Buttler makes no mistake. Chahal breaks the parntership. Faf had decided to go after the bowling no matter what. He drags the flighted delivery from outside off and swipes it towards long-on, Buttler moves to his left and takes a good catch. Not a fluent knock but he has laid the platform for the others. du Plessis c Buttler b Chahal 44(33) [4s-2 6s-2]
